Ifeanyi Onuba, Abuja The Minister of Industry, Trade and Investment, Richard Adebayo, has said that the Africa Continental Free Trade Area will improve the export quality of products manufactured in Nigeria. He said with the implementation of the agreement, there would be sophistication of exports across the continent. He added that this would provide manufacturers in Nigeria the opportunity to increase the quality of their products. Adebayo said these at an event to celebrate the 2019 African Industrialisation Day held in Calabar, Cross River State. The minister, according to a statement from the ministry, stated that the government was fully committed to resolving the constraints that might affect the business environment. Copyright PUNCH.
